ecific failure.","test_description":"Call merge function with two in-memory reviewer findings on the same clause (e.g., extractor=standard, risk=high risk) and assert merged report keeps both entries plus correct reviewer attribution metadata.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.74,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":8,"description":"End-to-end orchestration (dispatch all three reviewers, collect outputs, merge unified report) succeeds on a real contract without losing any reviewer findings.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is an end-to-end pipeline with multiple agentic steps (three live reviewers) plus aggregation; correctness depends on sequential orchestration and cross-step data retention. Lower levels miss failures like dropped findings between concurrent agentic results and merge. Rejected Agentic-only because the behavior explicitly requires multi-step orchestration across multiple reviewer calls.","test_description":"Execute full pipeline on real contracts with live extractor/risk/compliance reviewers in parallel, then assert final report contains every per-reviewer finding (no loss/overwrite), including conflicts preserved with attribution.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.12,"Workflow":0.83}}]}
